@pp_vox
title: <span style="color: var(--pp); font-style: italic;">National</span> <span style="color: var(--vox); font-style: italic;">Right</span> Coalition (PP - Vox)
subtitle: PP turns to Vox. [? if congreso_coalition_pp_vox_talks: And still needs every far-right vote it can find. ?]
view-if: congreso_coalition_pp_vox_s > congreso_s_majority - 50
choose-if: congreso_coalition_pp_vox_reach and not congreso_coalition_pp_cs_reach
unavailable-subtitle: [? if congreso_coalition_pp_cs_reach: The PP would rather govern with Cs than lean on Vox. ?][? if not congreso_coalition_pp_vox_reach: PP and Vox don't reach investiture even with the far right. ?]
on-arrival: {!
    // TODO — form the PP + Vox cabinet (only when the PP→Cs maths ISN'T there).
    //   • a Vox-tainted cabinet can't be negotiated upward (no rightvox escalation):
    //     pact-pragmatists and the Catalan right will NOT enable it — centralist
    //     right only. So this reaches far less often than the PP+Cs option.
!}

